{"questionId":"00907d99-e579-47a8-ac65-658aadef4aa7_2","correctAnswer":"24","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Apply the factoring from the given condition","content":"Note $42+6x = 6(7+x)$, and $7+x=4$."},{"title":"Compute the target value","content":"So $42+6x = 6 \\cdot 4 = 24$. The answer is <strong>24</strong>."}]}